HEADWORD: Lithodome
<hw>Lith"o*dome</hw> <pr>(-d⟦omac⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Litho-</ets> + Gr. <grk>do`mos</grk> house: cf. F.
<ets>lithodome</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of several
species of bivalves, which form holes in limestone, in which they live;
esp., any species of the genus <gen>Lithodomus</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lithodomous</ent>⟦br⟧
